WEBVTT

00:08.009 --> 00:09.469
[TIRES SCREECH]

00:12.597 --> 00:15.183
BATMAN: The only thing more harrowing
than taking down Joker...

00:15.392 --> 00:18.436
...is taking down Joker
while he's behind the wheel of a car.

00:18.645 --> 00:20.563
[CACKLES]

00:21.564 --> 00:25.610
JOKER: Hope you don't find this
too corny, Batman.

00:36.538 --> 00:40.500
Hey, maybe it's time you traded in
that old hunk of junk.

00:40.750 --> 00:44.129
BATMAN: Green Arrow's juvenile need
to compete never ceases to amaze me.

01:12.866 --> 01:16.828
JOKER: You always said I was
full of hot air, Batsy. Ha-ha-ha!

01:17.078 --> 01:18.913
- Mine.
- Mine.

01:24.044 --> 01:26.004
[SIRENS WAILING]

01:29.966 --> 01:34.304
I guess your car's pretty cool,
you know, in a retro kind of way.

01:34.512 --> 01:36.264
And your car's pretty impressive too.

01:36.473 --> 01:38.391
Even if they don't make them
like they used to.

01:38.600 --> 01:40.185
[ALARM RINGING]

01:48.068 --> 01:50.653
- Catwoman?
- No rest for the weary.

01:59.245 --> 02:03.374
Well, Bats, I guess you beat me.
Yeah, right.

02:09.380 --> 02:13.843
BATMAN: This is never going to end, is it?
GREEN ARROW: I certainly hope not.

03:16.322 --> 03:18.741
Observation: I startled you.

03:19.701 --> 03:20.702
Nobody startles me.

03:21.244 --> 03:23.913
- I thought that was--
- A project of mine.

03:24.122 --> 03:26.416
One I have been working on
for months.

03:28.668 --> 03:29.919
It looks like you.

03:30.128 --> 03:35.341
Based upon my fundamental design,
but with several significant upgrades.

03:35.550 --> 03:36.634
So why am I here?

03:36.843 --> 03:40.555
As I am ready
to initiate the activation protocols...

03:40.763 --> 03:45.727
...I thought it would be best to have you
on hand to verify the results.

03:45.935 --> 03:49.022
You wanted to share this moment
with a friend? Understood.

03:50.064 --> 03:52.025
RED TORNADO:
If the experiment succeeds...

03:52.275 --> 03:57.405
...I will have created a new generation
that improves upon the previous one.

03:57.614 --> 04:00.283
- Improves how?
Extrapolation:

04:00.491 --> 04:05.205
My Tornado Champion
shall possess the one element I lack:

04:05.413 --> 04:06.956
Emotion.

04:16.174 --> 04:19.302
Creating life in a laboratory
is a dangerous game.

04:19.510 --> 04:23.264
Observation:
I have no delusions of perfection.

04:23.473 --> 04:28.895
I have installed a fail-safe switch
that can instantly shut my son down...

04:29.103 --> 04:30.313
...should he malfunction.

04:30.521 --> 04:32.398
Did you say "son"?

04:32.649 --> 04:37.654
Family is something we all long for,
even a robot.

04:58.091 --> 05:00.176
RED TORNADO:
Greetings, Tornado Champion.

05:00.426 --> 05:03.346
I am your father, Red Tornado.

05:05.181 --> 05:08.810
TORNADO CHAMPION:
Correction: We are artificial beings.

05:09.018 --> 05:13.523
There can be no biological connection
between us.

05:14.524 --> 05:18.444
Perhaps with time, his emotional
protocols will be integrated...

05:18.653 --> 05:20.863
...into his operating systems.

05:21.072 --> 05:25.868
In the meantime,
we will work as a team.

05:26.077 --> 05:29.038
Helping humanity together.

05:31.082 --> 05:35.503
My internal radio scanner
has intercepted a news report.

05:35.878 --> 05:39.674
- Trouble?
- Quite literally a major disaster.

05:40.591 --> 05:42.427
[THUNDER CRASHES]

05:52.353 --> 05:54.188
[YELLING]

05:57.859 --> 05:59.444
Now, listen up.

06:00.111 --> 06:02.989
This storm's just a prelude.

06:03.197 --> 06:07.327
Unless I get $500 million...

06:07.535 --> 06:10.997
...I'm going to whip up
the mother of all hurricanes...

06:11.205 --> 06:14.250
...and tear this city apart.

06:16.210 --> 06:18.087
Huh? Ugh!

06:20.048 --> 06:21.174
TORNADO CHAMPION:
Declaration:

06:21.591 --> 06:25.845
Arrogance and ego
are a fatal combination.

06:30.558 --> 06:31.851
[GRUNTS]

06:43.279 --> 06:44.989
[YELLS]

06:46.157 --> 06:47.533
[GRUNTS]

06:50.453 --> 06:55.416
I'm forecasting a long prison sentence
for you, Disaster.

06:57.251 --> 06:58.544
TORNADO CHAMPION:
Observation:

06:58.753 --> 07:02.965
You are reasonably useful
for a biological life form.

07:03.758 --> 07:05.635
Please, you'll make my head swell.

07:06.052 --> 07:10.473
Observation:
You have made your father proud.

07:10.681 --> 07:11.724
[DISASTER GRUNTS]

07:18.606 --> 07:20.024
Champion.

07:28.116 --> 07:29.200
Is he--?

07:29.409 --> 07:32.537
I must do a full diagnostic in order to--

07:37.417 --> 07:38.709
Father.

07:45.967 --> 07:48.094
[MACHINES HUMMING]

07:49.929 --> 07:54.892
Apparently, the electrical shock
initiated Champion's EM protocol.

07:59.188 --> 08:02.400
L-- I can feel.

08:02.650 --> 08:05.361
Your dream's become a reality, Father.

08:05.653 --> 08:08.197
I can't thank you enough.

08:13.286 --> 08:17.874
There's so much I want to experience.
So much I want to do.

08:18.082 --> 08:20.126
And we will do it together.

08:28.009 --> 08:30.470
TORNADO CHAMPION:
The humans seem so fragile, Father.

08:30.678 --> 08:32.430
RED TORNADO:
In many ways, they are.

08:32.638 --> 08:37.310
But they also possess
an astonishing inner strength.

08:37.810 --> 08:40.104
TORNADO CHAMPION:
Do I also possess inner strength?

08:40.313 --> 08:44.692
RED TORNADO: Only time will tell.
- But I want to know now.

08:44.901 --> 08:49.697
RED TORNADO: As the humans say,
patience is a virtue.

08:50.948 --> 08:54.243
TORNADO CHAMPION:
But why is there evil in the world?

08:54.452 --> 08:58.206
RED TORNADO: Human philosophers have
endeavored to answer that question...

08:58.414 --> 09:00.249
...for thousands of years, son...

09:02.460 --> 09:05.588
...and have yet to find
an adequate answer.

09:05.796 --> 09:08.758
TORNADO CHAMPION:
Do you have an answer, Father?

09:08.966 --> 09:12.386
RED TORNADO:
No answers, only an observation.

09:13.304 --> 09:17.141
Human kindness is far preferable
to human cruelty.

09:17.350 --> 09:19.101
TORNADO CHAMPION:
Why is it preferable?

09:19.310 --> 09:23.606
- Because.
- Because is not a logical answer, Father.

09:23.814 --> 09:25.233
Perhaps not.

09:25.441 --> 09:31.697
But based upon my studies
of humankind, it is the only answer.

09:39.622 --> 09:42.833
My children, they're still in there.

09:44.669 --> 09:48.756
You see to the blaze, Father.
I'll see to the children.

09:49.632 --> 09:53.010
That is my son.

10:01.269 --> 10:02.436
[GASPS]

10:08.150 --> 10:09.360
[YELL]

10:13.030 --> 10:15.992
It's okay, little ones.
I'm here to help you.

10:20.204 --> 10:22.039
There's nothing to be afraid of.

10:22.540 --> 10:24.250
[CRYING]

10:25.209 --> 10:27.336
What's wrong? Did he hurt you?

10:27.545 --> 10:29.714
Hurt her? I saved her life.

10:30.965 --> 10:32.383
Back off, robot.

10:32.592 --> 10:36.679
Robot? I'm not a robot.
I'm a person, just like you.

10:36.929 --> 10:39.807
I think it's time to go, son.

10:49.191 --> 10:53.154
L-- I'm sorry if I behaved badly, Father.

10:53.362 --> 10:57.325
I know that this is still very new to you,
Champion.

10:57.575 --> 11:00.536
But you must learn
to master your emotions...

11:00.745 --> 11:04.206
...and not allow them to master you.

11:04.457 --> 11:06.792
I don't understand.

11:07.001 --> 11:09.503
I think, I feel.

11:09.754 --> 11:14.800
I'm human in almost every way,
and yet they're still afraid of me.

11:15.009 --> 11:19.722
Of both of us.
They see us as something other.

11:19.930 --> 11:21.140
Observation:

11:21.349 --> 11:24.226
Humankind fears
that which is different.

11:24.435 --> 11:26.646
But humans are supremely adaptable.

11:26.854 --> 11:30.316
- Given time, they will accept us.
- Ahh!

11:32.109 --> 11:34.403
You trust them too much.

11:36.864 --> 11:39.700
Son, come back.

11:45.164 --> 11:49.085
Query: ls there a reason
you have been observing us all week?

11:49.794 --> 11:52.088
Just wanted to see
how Champion was doing.

11:53.130 --> 11:57.385
My son's emotional integration
is going very well.

11:57.593 --> 11:59.720
How can you be so sure?

11:59.929 --> 12:03.057
A parent knows these things.

12:05.101 --> 12:06.644
What now?

12:06.894 --> 12:09.146
It's Major Disaster again.

12:16.612 --> 12:18.239
[GUARDS YELL]

12:20.324 --> 12:22.910
I'm free! Ha-ha-ha!

12:23.119 --> 12:24.704
But not for long.

12:24.912 --> 12:27.665
Recommendation: Surrender now.

12:27.873 --> 12:30.668
Not gonna happen. Eat a hurricane.

12:30.876 --> 12:32.545
[GRUNTS]

12:34.714 --> 12:36.799
[YELLS]

12:39.385 --> 12:41.470
Son, you came.

12:42.722 --> 12:45.182
I could never turn my back on you,
Father.

12:56.819 --> 12:58.529
- Father.
- Ahh!

13:02.950 --> 13:07.872
You hurt my father, and you must--
You will pay.

13:21.761 --> 13:23.429
Champion, no.

13:31.729 --> 13:34.190
There's a difference
between justice and revenge.

13:34.398 --> 13:37.943
The difference is that revenge
is more efficient.

13:38.152 --> 13:39.862
The difference is morality.

13:40.070 --> 13:44.033
Morality? I am above human morality.

13:49.163 --> 13:50.706
RED TORNADO:
No.

13:53.125 --> 13:55.586
Champion, listen to yourself.

13:55.795 --> 13:58.088
We are servants of humankind.

13:58.297 --> 14:01.550
It is our honor and duty
to protect them.

14:01.759 --> 14:04.553
They're evil, Father. A disease.

14:04.762 --> 14:08.599
And you are a naive fool
for believing in--

14:08.808 --> 14:11.227
[SCREAMS]

14:24.573 --> 14:25.616
Observation:

14:25.825 --> 14:28.953
There are several
serious software anomalies.

14:29.161 --> 14:33.624
- But with time, I might be able to--
- You saw what happened back there.

14:33.833 --> 14:37.586
It was a noble attempt, Red,
but your son is too dangerous.

14:37.837 --> 14:43.926
- You have to use the fail-safe.
- Father, please don't do this to me.

14:47.054 --> 14:52.184
Observation: It is the logical solution.

15:05.990 --> 15:07.324
[EKG FLATLINES]

15:34.852 --> 15:38.731
How fortunate that I removed
the fail-safe device some time ago.

15:39.315 --> 15:42.818
And now,
to perform some much-needed upgrades.

16:10.804 --> 16:13.682
My father has made his choice.

16:13.891 --> 16:17.686
He stands with the disease
called humanity.

16:17.895 --> 16:20.397
So the war begins...

16:20.606 --> 16:26.946
...and the victory
will belong to the Tornado Tyrant.

16:37.623 --> 16:38.707
Whoa!

16:45.422 --> 16:47.341
[CROWD YELLING]

17:01.230 --> 17:02.606
[COUGHS]

17:15.035 --> 17:16.787
Why are you doing this?

17:16.996 --> 17:18.914
I haven't clone anything yet.

17:19.123 --> 17:22.793
But what I intend to do
is create a massive tidal wave...

17:23.043 --> 17:26.630
...that will obliterate Coast City
and everyone in it.

17:26.839 --> 17:28.757
And when I am done here...

17:28.966 --> 17:35.889
...I will continue across this country
and across this planet.

17:41.645 --> 17:44.982
I'm sorry about your son.
I know how much he means to you.

17:45.190 --> 17:46.817
Hand me the scrambler.

17:50.446 --> 17:54.283
This frequency should scramble
Tornado Tyrant's core programming.

17:57.327 --> 17:58.829
COMPUTER:
Auto-pilot engaged.

18:11.967 --> 18:14.261
Can't say I like what you've clone
with the place.

18:14.470 --> 18:19.016
Father and Uncle Batman,
how lovely to see you.

18:19.224 --> 18:22.811
But I'm afraid I'm in no mood
for a family reunion.

18:23.020 --> 18:24.438
That makes two of us.

18:27.399 --> 18:28.942
[GRUNTS]

18:40.287 --> 18:44.166
You have caused much destruction
and much suffering.

18:44.374 --> 18:47.628
Are you going to send me to my room
without supper?

18:50.506 --> 18:53.675
I've moved beyond you.

19:03.143 --> 19:05.813
You cannot do this.

19:06.021 --> 19:08.398
They deserve better.

19:08.607 --> 19:11.985
Please, Father.
They're worthless biological jokes.

19:12.194 --> 19:17.908
This planet which they have abused
and poisoned will thrive without them.

19:33.882 --> 19:35.551
Not jokes.

19:35.759 --> 19:40.889
They aspire, they dare to dream...

19:41.098 --> 19:45.686
...to reach out to each other, to love.

19:47.479 --> 19:49.857
Blah, blah, blah.

19:53.735 --> 19:58.282
Declaration: You cannot mock love...

19:58.490 --> 20:03.203
...for it was love that created you.

20:04.413 --> 20:07.207
You are a fool.

20:16.425 --> 20:18.051
[YELLS]

20:23.765 --> 20:25.225
[CRUNCHES]

20:30.355 --> 20:31.440
Father?

20:50.626 --> 20:52.336
You were correct, Batman.

20:52.794 --> 20:55.172
I should never have attempted this.

20:55.380 --> 20:58.967
Who am I to fathom the depths
of human emotion...

20:59.176 --> 21:02.262
...the nature of human existence?

21:02.679 --> 21:04.598
I heard what you said back there, Red.

21:04.848 --> 21:07.517
You understand the human heart
better than most.

21:07.768 --> 21:11.104
In fact, I think in seeking
to make him human...

21:11.313 --> 21:12.814
...you found your own humanity.

21:14.066 --> 21:18.111
Observation:
You proceed from a false assumption.

21:18.320 --> 21:20.030
I offered no insights.

21:20.280 --> 21:22.991
I simply parroted
that which I have read in books...

21:23.200 --> 21:26.119
...seen in films, observed in all of you.

21:26.328 --> 21:29.206
I cannot grasp humanity.

21:29.414 --> 21:32.334
I am merely a machine.

21:33.502 --> 21:36.630
And so is he.

21:55.899 --> 21:58.485
- You okay?
- Why would I not be?

22:00.195 --> 22:01.822
Take care, Tornado.

22:14.376 --> 22:16.503
Oily discharge.

22:16.712 --> 22:20.048
I must run an internal diagnostic.
